      <scopecontent id="aspace_09eb7f3348eeb59730d430a39c68bc35">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>HAROLD J. MAYERS PAPERS, 1948-1976</p>
         <p>4 paige boxes; received from Harold J. Mayers</p>
         <p>The papers consist of correspondence, administrative files, subject files, printed materials and reports of Harold J. Mayers. The papers also contain files from six national and Washington, D.C., public health and tuberculosis organizations, including the American Public Health Association and National Tuberculosis Association. These papers form part of the Contemporary Medical Care and Health Policy Collection.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <bioghist id="aspace_28cfd040fef09e694dd1fe57f9e3d20a">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>Harold J. Mayers was a hospital consultant with the United Mine Workers of America Welfare and Retirement Fund from 1946 to 1976. The bulk of the papers consists of the correspondence files and administrative records from Mayers' tenure at the Fund. The early papers are fragmentary; the papers from 1973 to 1975 are more complete. In addition, the collection contains Mayers' files from five national and local (Washington, D.C.) public health and tuberculosis organizations.</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <accessrestrict id="aspace_4ac852b37abb65733c2f891129bd27f8">
         <head>Conditions Governing Access</head>
         <p>The materials are open for research.</p>  
      </accessrestrict>
